🛠️ Manual Testing — Crucial Tips & Notes

• Understand the user story and business goal before testing
• Think like an end-user; explore edge cases
• Use checklists to ensure consistency
• Document what you test (even exploratory sessions)
• Communicate bugs clearly with steps, evidence, and priority
• Regression testing matters — always recheck key flows
• Learn keyboard shortcuts and tools to increase speed
• Focus on quality, not quantity of test cases
• Pair up with developers to understand impact of changes
• Always validate acceptance criteria

Mindset:
Curiosity + Attention to detail + Empathy for the user = Great QA
